/**
 * This interface defines the communication  between the Save/Open engines and its client (Save/Open command).
 * <br><b>Role</b>: An Engine Listener is a communication pipe between an Engine and its client. 
 * <br>It has to be implemented by the Engine's client and used by the Engine.
 * <br>Its sends out information about :
 * <br>   - process progress
 * <br>   - elements treated by the process
 * <br>   - process incidents
 * <br>Any communication occurence through the listener, the client has the possibility to stop the process.
 * <br>EXCEPT FOR THE METHODS SUFFIXED WITH "_Freezing", THE LISTENER METHODS MUST RETURN IMMEDIATELY. 
 * <br>There can no be question to wait for an end user choice or whatever else.
 */
